Body:
Description: The webportal with all of our team members here has been having consistent issue where the sessions in end chrome. Just it will not notify us until we refresh the page. I won't capture setting changes and will happen while actively navigating around. 

We have been migrating this by using Edge, which seems to hold the session open and be fine.

Any assistance for this would be great, thank you for your time and consideration.
Next Steps Updated: I asked for details regarding the environment in order to investigate what could cause this issue on the server side.
What We've Learned Updated: The session is expiring in chrome and the changes are not applied upon saving.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Iosif Muntean, Lawrence Yeziorski

What We've Learned Updated: The session is expiring in chrome and the changes are not applied upon saving.

We had a remote session and performed the resources optimization procedure but the issue persists.

Next Steps Updated: I asked for details regarding the environment in order to investigate what could cause this issue on the server side.

We have asked for a new remote session with the customer.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Iosif Muntean, Flaviu Moldovan, Ramon Torres, Greg Golfes
Invitation updated. Attendees: Iosif Muntean, Flaviu Moldovan, Ramon Torres, Greg Golfes, Lawrence Yeziorski

What We've Learned Updated: The session is expiring in chrome and the changes are not applied upon saving.

We had a remote session and performed the resources optimization procedure but the issue persists.

We had another remote session with the customer and increased the PHP memory from 256 to 512MB. This seems to help, and we will check with the client next week.

Next Steps Updated: I asked for details regarding the environment in order to investigate what could cause this issue on the server side.

We have asked for a new remote session with the customer.

We will follow-up with the customer next week.
